stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE
    IDLE --> SELECTING: flush request or checkpoint pressure
    SELECTING --> REDO_WAIT: pageLSN greater than redo flushed
    SELECTING --> SNAPSHOTTING: redo durable
    REDO_WAIT --> SNAPSHOTTING: redo flushed
    REDO_WAIT --> SKIPPED: timeout or policy skip
    SNAPSHOTTING --> DOUBLEWRITE_WRITING: frame fixed or page image copied
    DOUBLEWRITE_WRITING --> DATAFILE_WRITING: doublewrite durable
    DATAFILE_WRITING --> VALIDATING: data page write complete
    VALIDATING --> MARK_CLEAN: frame unchanged since snapshot
    VALIDATING --> KEEP_DIRTY: newer modification exists
    MARK_CLEAN --> CHECKPOINT_NOTIFY: remove from flush list
    KEEP_DIRTY --> CHECKPOINT_NOTIFY: advance flushed page LSN only
    CHECKPOINT_NOTIFY --> RELEASED: notify redo checkpoint
    SKIPPED --> RELEASED
    RELEASED --> IDLE
    IDLE --> [*]

    note right of REDO_WAIT
        Flush wait holds only redo wait slot.
        It must not hold Buffer Pool list locks,
        page latch, file lock, or transaction lock.
    end note

    note right of DATAFILE_WRITING
        PageStore owns physical file locks.
        FlushCoordinator does not enter row-lock or MDL wait.
    end note

